                     <interp inst="t18210110-34-person352" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I found the stuffs at the house.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18210110-34-person353">
                  JAMES 
                  ALDOUS
               <interp inst="t18210110-34-person353" type="surname" value="ALDOUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-34-person353" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18210110-34-person353" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawbroker. On the 29th of October, the prisoner pledged a piece of cotton with me for 7 s. in his own name.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. About three weeks before Christmas, one Johnson, a licenced hawker, called and left these things in my care; he called again, said he was going in the country, and that he would fetch them on the 1st of January; whether he did or not I do not know as I was in confinement.</p>
               <p>
